refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns &true; if the reference was previously acquired and thus could be
 released, &false; otherwise.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Weakref::release example


<?php
class MyClass {
    public function __destruct() {
        echo "Destroying object!\n";
    }
}

$o1 = new MyClass;

$r1 = new Weakref($o1);

$r1->acquire();

echo "Unsetting o1...\n";
unset($o1);

$o2 = $r1->get();

$r1->release();

echo "Unsetting o2...\n";
unset($o2);
?>


    &example.outputs;


Unsetting o1...
Unsetting o2...
Destroying object!
